text: (upbeat music)
(bird chirping)

♪ Five little eggs were
sitting in a nest, ♪
♪ On top of the tree and all at rest. ♪
♪ Momma bird saw them starting to crack, ♪
♪ And soon all the eggs were hatched. ♪
(bird chirping)
(upbeat music continues)

♪ The first baby bird
looked down at the ground, ♪

♪ He got scared and
couldn't make a sound. ♪
♪ Momma bird said, "now fly, fly, fly." ♪

♪ But, the baby bird
was too shy, shy, shy. ♪
(bird chirping)
(upbeat music continues)

♪ The first baby bird
got out of the nest, ♪
♪ The next baby bird looked at the rest. ♪
♪ Momma bird said, "now, fly, fly, fly." ♪

♪ But, the baby bird
said, "oh, my, my, my." ♪
(birds chirping)
(upbeat music continues)
♪ The second baby bird flew way up high, ♪
♪ The next baby bird then gave a sigh. ♪
♪ Momma bird said, "now, fly, fly, fly." ♪

♪ But, the baby bird said,
"too high, high, high." ♪
(birds chirping)
(upbeat music continues)
♪ The third baby bird at last went out, ♪
♪ The next baby bird then gave a pout. ♪
♪ Momma bird said, "now, fly, fly, fly." ♪

♪ But the baby bird said,
"oh, why, why, why?" ♪
(birds chirping)
♪ The fourth baby bird went down to eat, ♪

♪ The last baby bird gave
a long, loud tweet. ♪
♪ Momma bird said, "now, fly, fly, fly." ♪

♪ But, the baby bird
wanted to cry, cry, cry. ♪
(birds chirping)
(upbeat music continues)
♪ Momma bird said, "it'll be okay, ♪

♪ You'll be all right
and there's a way." ♪

♪ The little baby bird
then started to sing ♪
♪ And flew off flapping his wings. ♪
(birds chirping)
(upbeat music continues)

♪ All the baby birds with
mother in the lead, ♪

♪ Flew through the sky
quite well indeed. ♪
♪ Momma bird said, "now, fly, fly, fly." ♪

♪ And all the birds flew
to the sky, sky, sky. ♪
(upbeat music continues)
